The paper investigates the presence and characteristics of cross-ecosystem software packages, which involves analyzing software development and evolution. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the distribution and packaging of software, which could fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. The paper also discusses the impact of cross-ecosystem packages on aspects such as security vulnerabilities and bugs, which could relate to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories. Finally, the paper mentions the popularity of cross-ecosystem packages with large developer communities, which could relate to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) category.
